com.logimethods.connector.nats.to_spark

Class NatsToSparkConnector<T,R,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.spark.streaming.receiver.Receiver<R>
      • com.logimethods.connector.nats.to_spark.NatsToSparkConnector<T,R,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OmnipotentNatsStreamingToSparkConnector, OmnipotentStandardNatsToSparkConnector

    public abstract class NatsToSparkConnector<T,R,V>
extends org.apache.spark.streaming.receiver.Receiver<R>
    A NATS to Spark Connector.

    It will transfer messages received from NATS into Spark data.

    That class extends Receiver<String>.

    An usage of this class would look like 

     JavaStreamingContext ssc = new JavaStreamingContext(sc, new Duration(2000));
 final JavaReceiverInputDStream<String> messages = 
                NatsToSparkConnector.receiveFromNats(String.class, StorageLevel.MEMORY_ONLY(), DEFAULT_SUBJECT)).asStreamOf(ssc);
    Author:
    Laurent Magnin
    See Also:
    (Java based) NATS / Spark Connectors, Spark Streaming Custom Receivers, Serialized Form
